    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-03-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-03-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="796"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d796">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Phelps</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 551.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-03-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 24, 1893</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your instruction No. 545, of the 8th instant, covering a very interesting
                    correspondence connected with the proposed change of officials in Samoa.</p>
                <p>I wish to express my appreciation of the thoughtfulness which furnishes me with
                    this information and so enables me in the informal discussions which are likely
                    to occur whenever I meet with Baron von Marschall or Sir Edward Malet, to take
                    intelligently such a part as may tend to promote the wishes of the Department. I
                    conceive that the President would be glad if, without any active interference on
                    our side, the English Government should reconsider its refusal to accept the
                    nomination of Mr. Hennings, and so end this matter by accepting both the
                    candidates proposed by the German Government and accepted by us.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wm. Walter Phelps.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
